        "content": "<p>I would like to use <code>Fin n</code> as a poset category (actually in my case, <code>Fin 2</code> is enough). I find it annoying to define functors from it. Could someone please help indicate what I should know in order to work with it?</p>\n<p>I would like these particular things:<br>\n-where is the instance saying \"any poset is a category\"? I do not know how to refer to the arrow <code>0 &lt;= 1</code>. <br>\n-An induction principle that helps me to define functors out of it would also be very helpful.<br>\n-examples of proofs/definitions using <code>Fin n</code> as categories.</p>\n<p>Any attempt to help is appreciated! Thanks in advance!</p>",
        "id": 496058979,
        "sender_full_name": "Yiming Xu",
        "timestamp": 1737965738
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Preorder.smallCategory#doc\">docs#Preorder.smallCategory</a> the instance you are looking for?</p>",
        "id": 496061309,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1737966537
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks! I see. It is called <code>homOfLE</code>.</p>",
        "id": 496062140,
        "sender_full_name": "Yiming Xu",
        "timestamp": 1737966814
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It would be even better if there are some works using <code>Fin n</code> in particular, since I expect this to be the canonical thing to use for, say, simplicial stuff. I will read this page. Many thanks!</p>",
        "id": 496062449,
